description:
&lt;p&gt;South Warwickshire Foundation Trust is currently looking for an enthusiastic and highly motivated Band 3 – Administration/Clerical Assistant to provide day to day support for leads, clinicians and patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is integral to the success and smooth running of this community team and is highly valued; we are a busy team that provide skilled nursing and therapy care within South Warwickshire Out of Hospital Care collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the team you will be liaising with GP’s, clinicians and other health and social care professionals on a daily basis and assisting with the day to day running of a demanding service. The successful candidate will need to be able to demonstrate previous appropriate experience, have excellent communication and computer skills, be motivated and have the desire to deliver high standards within a demanding environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are that successful person you will in return receive immense job satisfaction in your working environment, being a key person in a friendly and happy team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;South Warwickshire NHS Foundation Trust promotes flexible working options on all appropriate positions and our managers welcome these discussions during the recruitment process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTracy BirkettJob titleTherapy Team LeadEmail addresstracy.birkett@swft.nhs.ukTelephone number07500975474&lt;/p&gt;
